To download all the source code you need to type:

$ git clone https://github.com/mulatinho/sfm.git

If you want to support and make changes in this software with GDB support
the best way to build this project is just run 'make' against Makefile

$ cd sfm
$ make

If you wanna build a new release of HEAD version, you will have to do this:

$ cd sfm
$ aclocal
$ autoconf
$ automake --add-missing

To install this file manager when you get a official release you just need
to uncompress the TAR-file and run './configure' then 'make', to install this
software to all your users please run 'make install'

$ tar xfj sfm-version.tar.bz2
$ cd sfm-*

# if your system is 32 bits
$ ./configure --libdir=/usr/lib --prefix=/usr
# if your system is 64 bits
$ ./configure --libdir=/usr/lib64 --prefix=/usr

$ make

To install this software for all your users

$ sudo make install

Thanks for use SFM.
Alexandre Mulatinho.
